  <div class="step-1">
    <h3> 1. User Research </h3>
    <div class="divider2"> </div>
    <div class="project-description">
      We interviewed 9 UCSD students between the ages of 18-23 who regularly
      listened to music on their cell phone. Many of the questions involved
      playlist management, and if
      they had any struggle with their mobile phone application with playlists.
    </br></br>Example questions are listed below:
      <ol></br>
        <li> What music app do you use? </li>
        <li> Tell me about the last time you made a playlist. Why and
        how did you make it? </li>
        <li> List some times when you would make a playlist. </li>
        <li> Do you ever revise your playlist to keep them fresh or
          to remove songs you're tired of? </li>
        <li> How do you discover new music? </li>
      </ol>

      Moreover, we found 3 different user scenarios based on their each person's
      interview. Each scenario explains where, when, why, and how. From the
      interviews, we concluded that managing playlists on Spotify was the
      easiest, while Soundcloud was the most difficult. Apple Music was fairly
      new, so there were not many users. Soundcloud was mostly only used
      if Spotify did not have songs the user enjoyed.

    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="step-2">
    <h3> 2. Walkthrough & Scenario</h3>
    <div class="divider3"> </div>
    <div class="project-description">
      Clearly, there are many different ways a person can manage their playlists
      when using different applications. We picked 5 juicy scenarios and we
      showed the walkthroughs for Spotify, Apple Music, and Soundcloud.
      For this, we created a Google Sheet for each juicy scenario and placed
      each app's walkthrough the scenario in a side-by-side comparison.
      We listed screenshots and each action that was used.
    </br></br>
      Juicy Scenarios: </br></br>
      <ol>
        <li> Create a playlist for when you are hosting a party. </li>
        <li> Delete a whole playlist that you've created before. </li>
        <li> Delete songs off your own playlist. </li>
        <li> Create a playlist for songs you recently discovered. </li>
        <li> Go through another playlist and add it to your "party" playlist. </li>
      </ol>

